@103762 = ~Alatis' Guard~/*Torwächter*/
@103763 = ~Alatis Harbleton was one of the many halflings who had chosen a profession that was not to be mentioned in pleasant conversation. He had made a good career in Luskan, until a series of unpleasant events forced him to consider relocating to a new place.

Settling within the walls of the capital city of Waterdeep, he continued his activities. His willingness to act alone in making ill-gotten gains infuriated local guilds such as the infamous Night Masks, so he had to enlist a wizard to enchant his hood to protect himself from frequent attempts on his life.

Arrogant and confident in his invulnerability, he nevertheless got caught in a daring robbery and was caught by the guards. Unfortunately, his hood did not save him from the hangman's noose.

STATISTICS:

Equipped Abilities:
- Immunity to backstab
- Immunity to poison

Weight: 2

Usable By:
 Mage~/*Der Zwerg ist einer der vielen Bürger, die zu Beorunnas Brunnen gekommen sind, um sich um die vielen Bedürfnisse der Soldaten des Lagers zu kümmern. Der Stille Fürst nimmt viele in diesem Abschnitt der Aufnahme zu sich. Diejenigen, die er ausgewählt hat, ihm noch in dieser Welt zu dienen, die Überlebenden, fahren mit der Ausbildung fort. Ich bin ein Geist, verflucht, den Schöpfern so wie schon zu Lebzeiten auch im Tode als Sklave zu dienen. Meine Seele ist ewig gebunden an diesen Ort und die unverwundbaren Golems, die ich für die Meister erschaffen musste. Unglücklicherweise ist es auch fast das Äußerste, was wir tun können. Dennoch hoffe ich, dass es reicht. Dank Euch, <CHARNAME>. Dank Euch.*/
@103764 = ~Vial of Poison~/*Giftkegel*/
@103765 = ~In the absence of other arguments, poison becomes the best choice for most dark personalities. With skill, you can quickly and effectively turn your weapon into a poisoned weapon, even a small scratch from which becomes a festering wound, more dangerous than an axe blow.

This vial contains enough poison to coat a weapon once.

