@103861 = ~Zamithra~
@103862 = ~Amulet of Confidence~/*Amulett der Macht*/
@103863 = ~Several of these items were created at the request of Daern'on, the founder of the organization known in the dark elf world as the Azure Blades. They were intended to protect himself and his inner circle from treacherous attacks from unreliable allies.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
- Armor Class: +2
- Immunity to backstab~/*Der Wolf erinnert sich an das bisschen Blut an den kleinen Wunden der Kobolde, als diese in die Höhle rannten. Die aufgeblähten Leichen werden von einer Plane vor der Sonne geschützt. Ich hoffe Ihr kommt jetzt bald mal zum Punkt.*/
@103864 = ~Zamithras Edelstein~
@103865 = ~Das ist ein magischer Edelstein, der offenbar aus einem anderen, größeren Gegenstand herausgebrochen wurde. Er gehörte Zamithra, einer Söldnerin.~
@103866 = ~Great Zombie~/*Schwacher Zombie*/
@103867 = ~Hauswache~
@103868 = ~Aaa! Save yourselves! The cages are open!~/*Argh! Versteckt Euch. Ewiger Jubel!*/
@103869 = ~Run! The beasts are going to eat us now!~/*Laufen Die Jungs sind so blöd!*/
@103870 = ~Zor~
@103871 = ~You can earn money in Board Laid Bare Inn~/*Zur Blanken Planke*/
@103872 = ~This scroll should be used near the big tree at the Zoo in Blacklake. It won't work in this place.~/*Das ist der Schlüssel zum Elchstammportal. Was Interessantes hier?*/
@103873 = ~This scroll when read, removes protection from one of the room in Wanev's Tower. It won't work in this place.~/*Der kleine Augapfel stammt von einem der kleinen Baatezu-Quasits. Was Interessantes hier?*/
@103874 = ~Beschützer~
@103875 = ~This strange looking shield is woven from large intertwined branches with leaves. The unusual shape and size of these leaves suggest that they were taken from ancient oaks growing deep in the Forest of Mir. If you examine it closely, you will find powerful druidic charms emanating from the surface of the shield that increase the wearer's health and heal their wounds more quickly. Every morning, at sunrise, one of the branches will flare faintly for a moment. Then it can be taken and planted in the ground, and another will immediately grow in its place. After the proper sorcery is recited, the planted branch transforms into a fearsome Shambler, whose strength and size depends on the Druid's skill. Because of its unique origin, the power of this shield can only be utilized by the most dedicated followers of Nature.

STATISTICS:

Equipped abilities:
- Maximum HP: +5
- Regenerates 1 HP every 6 seconds

Charge abilities:
- Summon Shambling Mound once per day

Armor Class: +2
Weight: 1
Requirements: 12 Wisdom and 15 Charisma

Usable By:
 Druid~/*Der Sklavin, die Ihr aus den Händen der Illithiden befreit habt, ist es gelungen, sich bis zum Lager der Seherin vorzukämpfen. Wenn die Bedrohung durch die Valsharess erst einmal gebannt ist, will die Seherin ihr helfen, an die Oberwelt zurückzukehren und das Unterreich ein für alle Mal zu verlassen. Der Ochse wünschte, Ihr würdet das Tor öffnen, damit er frei wäre. Dann betrachtet er den ganzen Sand um sich herum und ändert schnell seine Meinung. Nachdem ein Weißer Slaad ein Jahrhundert lang überlebt hat, verwandelt er sich in einen noch größeren und stärken Slaad: in einen Schwarzen Slaad. Nun, die magische Kraft in dieser Gegend soll unermesslich sein. Es gibt Monolithen dort, denen darf man sich nicht nähern, so gefährlich sind sie... was meinen Verdacht, die Worte dort finden zu können, eher noch verstärkt.*/
@103876 = ~Protector +3~/*Beschützer*/
@103877 = ~This strange looking shield is woven from large intertwined branches with leaves. The unusual shape and size of these leaves suggest that they were taken from ancient oaks growing deep in the Forest of Mir. If you examine it closely, you will find powerful druidic charms emanating from the surface of the shield that increase the wearer's health and heal their wounds more quickly. Every morning, at sunrise, one of the branches will flare faintly for a moment. Then it can be taken and planted in the ground, and another will immediately grow in its place. After the proper sorcery is recited, the planted branch transforms into a fearsome Shambler, whose strength and size depends on the Druid's skill. Because of its unique origin, the power of this shield can only be utilized by the most dedicated followers of Nature.

